<br>
Qeynos Afternoon Tea: +5 DEX, +5 WIS, +5 INT, +5 AGI, miraculous drink.<br>
<br>
Fizzy Odus Juice: +4 AGI, +4 DEX, +4 INT, Flowing Drink<br>
<br>
Grobb Liquidised Meat: +6 STR, +6 STA, -1 WIS, -1 INT, Miraculous Drink<br>
<br>
Innothule Triple Bile: +5 SvM<br>
<br>
Karana Brown Tea: +1 SvP (We QAT brewers will hate you if you make/sell this ;-)  )<br>
<br>
Sylvan Berry Juice: +1 AGI<br>
<br>
Orange Juice: +1 SvD<br>
<br>
Kaladim Constitutional: +5 STA, +5 to all saves, Miraculous drink<br>
<br>
Surefall Ranger's Trail Juice: +4 DEX, +4 STA, +4 WIS<br>
<br>
Other than the Karana Brown Tea and the juices, these are all time-consuming and expensive to make. All but the SRTJ and the QAT require a corking device (needs a blue diamond) to make, and most are trivial in Grandmaster territory.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps,<br>
Chase<br>
The slightly less grumpy ranger<br>
